River Dreams
============

A simple prompt for the ZSH shell with a tribal design.

You can have a preview in the preview.webp file.

Features
--------

It displays:

    - Your local IPV4 address.
    - The disk use percentage.
    - The date, hour and minute.
    - A decorator when root.
    - A decorator for exit codes.
    - The directory name.


Requirements
------------

In order to build it, you will simply need a C compiler, like GCC, and be using
a font patched by the Nerd Fonts project.

Installation
------------

- Compile the file riverdreams.c.

    gcc riverdreams.c -O3 -o riverdreams

- Make its output be your ZSH prompt by editing your ~/.zshrc file. Replace
  <DIR> by the path for the repository.

    setopt promptsubst
    PROMPT='$(<DIR>/riverdreams)'

- Reopen ZSH.
